<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1740&amp;p=15000#p15000"><![CDATA[
Dragon Quest requires Frame IRQs for sound, but will still run without them. I believe this is also the case for a few other Dragon Quest games.<br /><br />The MMC5 Mahjong game also requires Frame IRQs for sound and <strong>will not run without them</strong> (it will hang indefinitely at the titlescreen).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Tue Jul 04, 2006 2:07 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
